WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 754
Chapter 754
(Senate Bill 729)
AN ACT concerning
Real Property – Access to Counsel in Evictions Program and Mobile Home
Parks – Expansion
FOR the purpose of altering the Access to Counsel in Evictions Program to expand access
to legal representation and other services under the Program to individuals who
occupy premises of a mobile home park; authorizing a prospective resident of a
mobile home park to bring a certain action against a park owner under certain
circumstances; altering certain provisions of law related to tenancies, rental
agreements, rental agreement offers, and notice requirements between park owners,
residents, qualified residents, and subtenants; requiring a park owner to establish a
certain pet policy for the residents of the park on or before a certain date; establishing
certain requirements and prohibitions related to park fees and utility fees imposed
by a park owner; prohibiting a utility vendor from billing certain residents in a
certain manner and establishing certain notice requirements for the utility vendor;
prohibiting a park owner from denying or limiting certain privileges of a mobile home
park because of the nonpayment of rent by a resident or certain characteristics of a
person; requiring a park owner to ensure each resident has access to a water supply
that meets certain standards; altering the grounds for eviction from a mobile home
park; establishing a certain time period for a resident to cure the nonpayment of
rent; requiring a park owner to join a known subtenant as a defendant in an action
for repossession of the premises; prohibiting a park owner from repossessing the
premises of a subtenant except under certain circumstances; establishing certain
procedures and requirements for the execution of a warrant for repossession related
to the appeal of a judgment and the repossession of the premises by a park owner;
and generally relating to the Access to Counsel in Evictions Program and mobile
home parks.
BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
Article – Real Property
Section 8–901, and 8–904 through 8–907, 8A–101, 8A–201, 8A–202, 8A–301,
8A–401, 8A–402, 8A–501, 8A–503, 8A–604, 8A–801, 8A–1001(a)(1), 8A–1101,
8A–1301, 8A–1502, and 8A–1701 through 8A–1703
Annotated Code of Maryland
(2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
Article – Real Property
Section 8–903
Annotated Code of Maryland
(2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
