THE PEACE AND QUIET OF OTHER RESIDENTS; OR
2. WILLFULLY AND REPEATEDLY DISREGARDING THE
RULES OF THE RENTAL AGREEMENT.
(2) “SUBSTANTIAL VIOLATION” DOES NOT INCLUDE A VIOLATION OF
A PROVISION OF THE PARK RULES OR THE RENTAL AGREEMENT THAT A COURT
DETERMINES TO BE UNCONSCIONABLE IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 8A–1502 OF THIS
TITLE.
