8A–201.
(a) Before a current or prospective resident signs a rental agreement or occupies
the premises, a park owner shall:
(1) (I) Provide the prospective resident with a written notice identifying
the availability[,] AND capacity[, and connection fee] of all utility services at the proposed
site in order to assure the proper and adequate installation of the mobile home.
