(c) Except if a material change results in the deterioration of the home, a park
owner may not charge a fee for inspecting a home for resale more than one time within a
12–month period.
(d) The fee for inspecting a home for resale may not exceed $60.
(E) (1) IF A VIOLATION OF A PARK RULE CAUSES ACTUAL DAMAGES, A
PARK OWNER MAY IMPOSE A FEE IN AN AMOUNT NOT TO EXCEED THE COSTS
INCURRED BY THE VIOLATION.
(2) ON REQUEST, A PARK OWNER SHALL PROVIDE A RESIDENT WITH
ADEQUATE DOCUMENTATION TO SUPPORT THE ASSESSMENT AND THE AMOUNT OF
THE FEE.
(F) A RESIDENT MAY DISPUTE THE IMPOSITION OF A FEE IN A
REPOSSESSION PROCEEDING UNDER SUBTITLE 17 OF THIS TITLE.
